83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
House Bill 4137
Sponsored by Representative CATE, Senator GIROD, Representatives RIEKE SMITH, PHAM H, SANCHEZ; Rep-
resentatives GOMBERG, HELFRICH, HELM, JAVADI, LEVY B, LEWIS, MANNIX, MCLAIN, RESCHKE,
SKARLATOS, WALTERS, WISE, Senators GELSER BLOUIN, HAYDEN, NASH, PHAM K, ROBINSON,
SOLLMAN, THATCHER (Presession filed.)
SUMMARY
The following summary is not prepared by the sponsors of the measure and is not a part of the body thereof subject
to consideration by the Legislative Assembly. It is an editor’s brief statement of the essential features of the
measure as introduced. The statement includes a measure digest written in compliance with applicable readability
standards.
Digest: If a traffic ticket is sent to a person who sold a car before the traffic offense happened,
the old owner may let the court know that they are not required to pay the ticket. (Flesch Read-
ability Score: 62.5).
Provides that, in lieu of making a first appearance for a traffic violation citation, the person
who is the previous owner of a vehicle may notify the court that the person has transferred interest
in the vehicle and is not liable for the citation.
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT
2 Relating to the transfer of interest in motor vehicles; creating new provisions; and amending ORS
3 153.061.
4 Be It Enacted by the People of the State of Oregon:
5 SECTION 1. ORS 153.061 is amended to read:
6 153.061. (1) Except as provided in subsection (2) or (8) of this section, a defendant who has been
7 issued a violation citation must either:
8 (a) Make a first appearance by personally appearing in court at the time indicated in the sum-
9 mons; or
10 (b) Make a first appearance in the manner provided in subsection (3) of this section before the
11 time indicated in the summons.
12 (2) If a defendant is issued a violation citation for careless driving under ORS 811.135 on which
13 a police officer noted that the offense contributed to an accident and that the cited offense appears
14 to have contributed to the serious physical injury or death of a vulnerable user of a public way, the
15 officer may not enter the amount of the presumptive fine on the summons and the defendant must
16 make a first appearance by personally appearing in court at the time indicated in the summons.
17 (3)(a) Except as provided in this section, a defendant who has been issued a violation citation
18 may make a first appearance in the matter before the time indicated in the summons by one of the
19 following means:
20 (A) The defendant may submit to the court a written or oral request for a trial.
21 (B) The defendant may enter a plea of no contest by:
22 (i) Delivering to the court, a Central Violations Bureau established under ORS 153.806 or a Vi-
23 olations Bureau established by the court under ORS 153.800 the summons and a check or money
24 order in the amount of the presumptive fine set forth in the summons; or
25 (ii) Appearing by electronic or telephonic means and entering the plea with a Central Violations
26 Bureau established under ORS 153.806 or a Violations Bureau established by the court under ORS
27 153.800.
NOTE: Matter in boldfaced type in an amended section is new; matter [italic and bracketed] is existing law to be omitted.
New sections are in boldfaced type.
